get.description:
This endpoint checks whether a wallet address holds a specific NFT or if a wallet address holds any NFT from a given collection. 
 
 If tokenId is entered, the endpoint will check if the wallet address holds that exact NFT. While if tokenId is omitted, the endpoint will check if the wallet address holds any NFT from the entered collection.

parameters.name: chainId
parameters.description: Unique identifier for a blockchain network.

parameters.name: contractAddress
parameters.description: The address of the NFT collection to query.

parameters.name: walletAddress
parameters.description: The address of the wallet to query.

parameters.name: tokenId
parameters.description: The ID of the token. This parameter is supported by Tatum and Covalent (When entered, the endpoint will check if the wallet address holds the specific NFT ID specified.)

parameters.name: includeRaw
parameters.description: Returns the raw data given by the provider. WARNING: removes backup feature, and raw data returned is not normalized which might make switching providers difficult

parameters.name: provider
parameters.description: Specify which provider to use. The project's provider priority list is used by default if no providers are selected. (Priority list can be managed on Uniblock's dashboard)

webhookSecret.description: We will sign messages sent to webhookUrl using webhookSecret. webhookSecret will be autogenerated if not specified. The secret should only contain alphanumeric characters [A-Za-z0-9]. Min/Max length: [32,64]. Recommended length: 32. webhookSecret will be stored in base64

metadata.description: Additional metadata to be returned alongside a webhook response.

filter.description: An object representing the desired filters.

addChainIds.description: Add unique identifiers for blockchain networks.

removeChainIds.description: Remove unique identifiers for blockchain networks.

walletAddresses.description: Set addresses watched by wallet event.

addWalletAddresses.description: Add addresses watched by wallet event.

removeWalletAddresses.description: Remove addresses watched by wallet event.

contractAddresses.description: Set contract addresses for a webhook. Input format is `{chain}.{address}`

addContractAddresses.description: Addresses to add from webhook. Input format is `{chain}.{address}`

removeContractAddresses.description: Addresses to remove from webhook. Input format is `{chain}.{address}`

removeCollectionIds.description: Collection Ids to remove from monitoring.

nftIds.description: NFT Ids to monitor. Input format is `{chain}.{contract}.{token_id}` for EVM chains, `{chain}.{token_id}` for Solana

addNftIds.description: Addtional NFT Ids to monitor. Input format is `{chain}.{contract}.{token_id}` for EVM chains, `{chain}.{token_id}` for Solana

removeNftIds.description: NFT Ids to remove from monitoring. Input format is `{chain}.{contract}.{token_id}` for EVM chains, `{chain}.{token_id}` for Solana
